Affine Cipher: The affine cipher takes each character and converts it into a numeric value and multiplies it by the a value then adds the b value and reduces it modulo 26.
So the formula is essentially:
f(x) = ( a(x) + b ) % 26
*where X is the alphabetical index of the letter 0 - 25

ADFGVX Code: The ADFGVX cipher uses two encryption keys and encrypts your message using the letters A D F G V X. The entire process is quite complicated, a more thorough explanation can be found here:
http://practicalcryptography.com/ciphers/adfgvx-cipher/
